Body.Description: Microsoft Hyper-V Network Adapter

Body.Caption: Application Experience
Body.Description: Processes application compatibility cache requests for applications as they are launched
Body.Name: AeLookupSvc

Body.Caption: Application Layer Gateway Service
Body.Description: Provides support for 3rd party protocol plug-ins for Internet Connection Sharing
Body.Name: ALG

Body.Caption: Application Host Helper Service
Body.Description: Provides administrative services for IIS, for example configuration history and Application Pool account mapping. If this service is stopped, configuration history and locking down files or directories with Application Pool specific Access Control Entries will not work.
Body.Name: AppHostSvc

Body.Caption: Application Identity
Body.Description: Determines and verifies the identity of an application. Disabling this service will prevent AppLocker from being enforced.
Body.Name: AppIDSvc

Body.Caption: Application Information
Body.Description: Facilitates the running of interactive applications with additional administrative privileges.  If this service is stopped, users will be unable to launch applications with the additional administrative privileges they may require to perform desired user tasks.
Body.Name: Appinfo

Body.Caption: Application Management
Body.Description: Processes installation, removal, and enumeration requests for software deployed through Group Policy. If the service is disabled, users will be unable to install, remove, or enumerate software deployed through Group Policy. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: AppMgmt

Body.Caption: App Readiness
Body.Description: Gets apps ready for use the first time a user signs in to this PC and when adding new apps.
Body.Name: AppReadiness

Body.Caption: AppX Deployment Service (AppXSVC)
Body.Description: Provides infrastructure support for deploying Store applications. This service is started on demand and if disabled Store applications will not be deployed to the system, and may not function properly.
Body.Name: AppXSvc

Body.Caption: ASP.NET State Service
Body.Description: Provides support for out-of-process session states for ASP.NET. If this service is stopped, out-of-process requests will not be processed. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: aspnet_state

Body.Caption: Windows Audio Endpoint Builder
Body.Description: Manages audio devices for the Windows Audio service.  If this service is stopped, audio devices and effects will not function properly.  If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start
Body.Name: AudioEndpointBuilder

Body.Caption: Windows Audio
Body.Description: Manages audio for Windows-based programs.  If this service is stopped, audio devices and effects will not function properly.  If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start
Body.Name: Audiosrv

Body.Caption: Base Filtering Engine
Body.Description: The Base Filtering Engine (BFE) is a service that manages firewall and Internet Protocol security (IPsec) policies and implements user mode filtering. Stopping or disabling the BFE service will significantly reduce the security of the system. It will also result in unpredictable behavior in IPsec management and firewall applications.
Body.Name: BFE

Body.Caption: Background Intelligent Transfer Service
Body.Description: Transfers files in the background using idle network bandwidth. If the service is disabled, then any applications that depend on BITS, such as Windows Update or MSN Explorer, will be unable to automatically download programs and other information.
Body.Name: BITS

Body.Caption: Background Tasks Infrastructure Service
Body.Description: Windows infrastructure service that controls which background tasks can run on the system.
Body.Name: BrokerInfrastructure

Body.Caption: Computer Browser
Body.Description: Maintains an updated list of computers on the network and supplies this list to computers designated as browsers. If this service is stopped, this list will not be updated or maintained. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: Browser

Body.Caption: Certificate Propagation
Body.Description: Copies user certificates and root certificates from smart cards into the current user's certificate store, detects when a smart card is inserted into a smart card reader, and, if needed, installs the smart card Plug and Play minidriver.
Body.Name: CertPropSvc

Body.Caption: COM+ System Application
Body.Description: Manages the configuration and tracking of Component Object Model (COM)+-based components. If the service is stopped, most COM+-based components will not function properly. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: COMSysApp

Body.Caption: Cryptographic Services
Body.Description: Provides three management services: Catalog Database Service, which confirms the signatures of Windows files and allows new programs to be installed; Protected Root Service, which adds and removes Trusted Root Certification Authority certificates from this computer; and Automatic Root Certificate Update Service, which retrieves root certificates from Windows Update and enable scenarios such as SSL. If this service is stopped, these management services will not function properly. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: CryptSvc

Body.Caption: DCOM Server Process Launcher
Body.Description: The DCOMLAUNCH service launches COM and DCOM servers in response to object activation requests. If this service is stopped or disabled, programs using COM or DCOM will not function properly. It is strongly recommended that you have the DCOMLAUNCH service running.
Body.Name: DcomLaunch

Body.Caption: Optimize drives
Body.Description: Helps the computer run more efficiently by optimizing files on storage drives.
Body.Name: defragsvc

Body.Caption: Device Association Service
Body.Description: Enables pairing between the system and wired or wireless devices.
Body.Name: DeviceAssociationService

Body.Caption: Device Install Service
Body.Description: Enables a computer to recognize and adapt to hardware changes with little or no user input. Stopping or disabling this service will result in system instability.
Body.Name: DeviceInstall

Body.Caption: DHCP Client
Body.Description: Registers and updates IP addresses and DNS records for this computer. If this service is stopped, this computer will not receive dynamic IP addresses and DNS updates. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: Dhcp

Body.Caption: Diagnostics Tracking Service
Body.Description: The Diagnostics Tracking Service enables data collection about functional issues in Windows components.
Body.Name: DiagTrack

Body.Caption: DNS Client
Body.Description: The DNS Client service (dnscache) caches Domain Name System (DNS) names and registers the full computer name for this computer. If the service is stopped, DNS names will continue to be resolved. However, the results of DNS name queries will not be cached and the computer's name will not be registered. If the service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: Dnscache

Body.Caption: Wired AutoConfig
Body.Description: The Wired AutoConfig (DOT3SVC) service is responsible for performing IEEE 802.1X authentication on Ethernet interfaces. If your current wired network deployment enforces 802.1X authentication, the DOT3SVC service should be configured to run for establishing Layer 2 connectivity and/or providing access to network resources. Wired networks that do not enforce 802.1X authentication are unaffected by the DOT3SVC service.
Body.Name: dot3svc

Body.Caption: Diagnostic Policy Service
Body.Description: The Diagnostic Policy Service enables problem detection, troubleshooting and resolution for Windows components.  If this service is stopped, diagnostics will no longer function.
Body.Name: DPS

Body.Caption: Device Setup Manager
Body.Description: Enables the detection, download and installation of device-related software. If this service is disabled, devices may be configured with outdated software, and may not work correctly.
Body.Name: DsmSvc

Body.Caption: Extensible Authentication Protocol
Body.Description: The Extensible Authentication Protocol (EAP) service provides network authentication in such scenarios as 802.1x wired and wireless, VPN, and Network Access Protection (NAP).  EAP also provides application programming interfaces (APIs) that are used by network access clients, including wireless and VPN clients, during the authentication process.  If you disable this service, this computer is prevented from accessing networks that require EAP authentication.
Body.Name: Eaphost

Body.Caption: Encrypting File System (EFS)
Body.Description: Provides the core file encryption technology used to store encrypted files on NTFS file system volumes. If this service is stopped or disabled, applications will be unable to access encrypted files.
Body.Name: EFS

Body.Caption: Windows Event Log
Body.Description: This service manages events and event logs. It supports logging events, querying events, subscribing to events, archiving event logs, and managing event metadata. It can display events in both XML and plain text format. Stopping this service may compromise security and reliability of the system.
Body.Name: EventLog

Body.Caption: COM+ Event System
Body.Description: Supports System Event Notification Service (SENS), which provides automatic distribution of events to subscribing Component Object Model (COM) components. If the service is stopped, SENS will close and will not be able to provide logon and logoff notifications. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: EventSystem

Body.Caption: Function Discovery Provider Host
Body.Description: The FDPHOST service hosts the Function Discovery (FD) network discovery providers. These FD providers supply network discovery services for the Simple Services Discovery Protocol (SSDP) and Web Services – Discovery (WS-D) protocol. Stopping or disabling the FDPHOST service will disable network discovery for these protocols when using FD. When this service is unavailable, network services using FD and relying on these discovery protocols will be unable to find network devices or resources.
Body.Name: fdPHost

Body.Caption: Function Discovery Resource Publication
Body.Description: Publishes this computer and resources attached to this computer so they can be discovered over the network.  If this service is stopped, network resources will no longer be published and they will not be discovered by other computers on the network.
Body.Name: FDResPub

Body.Caption: Windows Font Cache Service
Body.Description: Optimizes performance of applications by caching commonly used font data. Applications will start this service if it is not already running. It can be disabled, though doing so will degrade application performance.
Body.Name: FontCache

Body.Caption: Windows Presentation Foundation Font Cache 3.0.0.0
Body.Description: Optimizes performance of Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) applications by caching commonly used font data. WPF applications will start this service if it is not already running. It can be disabled, though doing so will degrade the performance of WPF applications.
Body.Name: FontCache3.0.0.0

Body.Caption: Microsoft FTP Service
Body.Description: Enables this server to be a File Transfer Protocol (FTP) server. If this service is stopped, the server cannot function as an FTP server. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: ftpsvc

Body.Caption: Group Policy Client
Body.Description: The service is responsible for applying settings configured by administrators for the computer and users through the Group Policy component. If the service is disabled, the settings will not be applied and applications and components will not be manageable through Group Policy. Any components or applications that depend on the Group Policy component might not be functional if the service is disabled.
Body.Name: gpsvc

Body.Caption: Google Update Service (gupdate)
Body.Description: Keeps your Google software up to date. If this service is disabled or stopped, your Google software will not be kept up to date, meaning security vulnerabilities that may arise cannot be fixed and features may not work. This service uninstalls itself when there is no Google software using it.
Body.Name: gupdate

Body.Caption: Google Update Service (gupdatem)
Body.Description: Keeps your Google software up to date. If this service is disabled or stopped, your Google software will not be kept up to date, meaning security vulnerabilities that may arise cannot be fixed and features may not work. This service uninstalls itself when there is no Google software using it.
Body.Name: gupdatem

Body.Caption: Human Interface Device Service
Body.Description: Activates and maintains the use of hot buttons on keyboards, remote controls, and other multimedia devices. It is recommended that you keep this service running.
Body.Name: hidserv

Body.Caption: Health Key and Certificate Management
Body.Description: Provides X.509 certificate and key management services for the Network Access Protection Agent (NAPAgent). Enforcement technologies that use X.509 certificates may not function properly without this service
Body.Name: hkmsvc

Body.Caption: Internet Explorer ETW Collector Service
Body.Description: ETW Collector Service for Internet Explorer. When running, this service collects real time ETW events and processes them.
Body.Name: IEEtwCollectorService

Body.Caption: IIS Admin Service
Body.Description: Enables this server to administer the IIS metabase. The IIS metabase stores configuration for the SMTP and FTP services. If this service is stopped, the server will be unable to configure SMTP or FTP. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: IISADMIN

Body.Caption: IKE and AuthIP IPsec Keying Modules
Body.Description: The IKEEXT service hosts the Internet Key Exchange (IKE) and Authenticated Internet Protocol (AuthIP) keying modules. These keying modules are used for authentication and key exchange in Internet Protocol security (IPsec). Stopping or disabling the IKEEXT service will disable IKE and AuthIP key exchange with peer computers. IPsec is typically configured to use IKE or AuthIP; therefore, stopping or disabling the IKEEXT service might result in an IPsec failure and might compromise the security of the system. It is strongly recommended that you have the IKEEXT service running.
Body.Name: IKEEXT

Body.Caption: IP Helper
Body.Description: Provides tunnel connectivity using IPv6 transition technologies (6to4, ISATAP, Port Proxy, and Teredo), and IP-HTTPS. If this service is stopped, the computer will not have the enhanced connectivity benefits that these technologies offer.
Body.Name: iphlpsvc

Body.Caption: Windows Phone IP over USB Transport (IpOverUsbSvc)
Body.Description: Enables communication between the Windows SDK and a Windows Device. If the service is stopped, application deployment and debugging will fail on device.
Body.Name: IpOverUsbSvc

Body.Caption: CNG Key Isolation
Body.Description: The CNG key isolation service is hosted in the LSA process. The service provides key process isolation to private keys and associated cryptographic operations as required by the Common Criteria. The service stores and uses long-lived keys in a secure process complying with Common Criteria requirements.
Body.Name: KeyIso

Body.Caption: KDC Proxy Server service (KPS)
Body.Description: KDC Proxy Server service runs on edge servers to proxy Kerberos protocol messages to domain controllers on the corporate network.
Body.Name: KPSSVC

Body.Caption: KtmRm for Distributed Transaction Coordinator
Body.Description: Coordinates transactions between the Distributed Transaction Coordinator (MSDTC) and the Kernel Transaction Manager (KTM). If it is not needed, it is recommended that this service remain stopped. If it is needed, both MSDTC and KTM will start this service automatically. If this service is disabled, any MSDTC transaction interacting with a Kernel Resource Manager will fail and any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: KtmRm

Body.Caption: Server
Body.Description: Supports file, print, and named-pipe sharing over the network for this computer. If this service is stopped, these functions will be unavailable. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: LanmanServer

Body.Caption: Workstation
Body.Description: Creates and maintains client network connections to remote servers using the SMB protocol. If this service is stopped, these connections will be unavailable. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: LanmanWorkstation

Body.Caption: Link-Layer Topology Discovery Mapper
Body.Description: Creates a Network Map, consisting of PC and device topology (connectivity) information, and metadata describing each PC and device.  If this service is disabled, the Network Map will not function properly.
Body.Name: lltdsvc

Body.Caption: TCP/IP NetBIOS Helper
Body.Description: Provides support for the NetBIOS over TCP/IP (NetBT) service and NetBIOS name resolution for clients on the network, therefore enabling users to share files, print, and log on to the network. If this service is stopped, these functions might be unavailable. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: lmhosts

Body.Caption: Local Session Manager
Body.Description: Core Windows Service that manages local user sessions. Stopping or disabling this service will result in system instability.
Body.Name: LSM

Body.Caption: Multimedia Class Scheduler
Body.Description: Enables relative prioritization of work based on system-wide task priorities. This is intended mainly for multimedia applications.  If this service is stopped, individual tasks resort to their default priority.
Body.Name: MMCSS

Body.Caption: Mozilla Maintenance Service
Body.Description: The Mozilla Maintenance Service ensures that you have the latest and most secure version of Mozilla Firefox on your computer. Keeping Firefox up to date is very important for your online security, and Mozilla strongly recommends that you keep this service enabled.
Body.Name: MozillaMaintenance

Body.Caption: Windows Firewall
Body.Description: Windows Firewall helps protect your computer by preventing unauthorized users from gaining access to your computer through the Internet or a network.
Body.Name: MpsSvc

Body.Caption: Distributed Transaction Coordinator
Body.Description: Coordinates transactions that span multiple resource managers, such as databases, message queues, and file systems. If this service is stopped, these transactions will fail. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: MSDTC

Body.Caption: SQL Server Integration Services 13.0
Body.Description: Provides management support for SSIS package storage and execution.
Body.Name: MsDtsServer130

Body.Caption: Microsoft iSCSI Initiator Service
Body.Description: Manages Internet SCSI (iSCSI) sessions from this computer to remote iSCSI target devices. If this service is stopped, this computer will not be able to login or access iSCSI targets. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: MSiSCSI

Body.Caption: Windows Installer
Body.Description: Adds, modifies, and removes applications provided as a Windows Installer (*.msi, *.msp) package. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: msiserver

Body.Caption: MS-MPI Launch Service
Body.Description: Service for launching MS-MPI applications
Body.Name: MsMpiLaunchSvc

Body.Caption: SQL Full-text Filter Daemon Launcher (MSSQLSERVER)
Body.Description: Service to launch full-text filter daemon process which will perform document filtering and word breaking for SQL Server full-text search. Disabling this service will make full-text search features of SQL Server unavailable.
Body.Name: MSSQLFDLauncher

Body.Caption: SQL Server Launchpad (MSSQLSERVER)
Body.Description: Service to launch Advanced Analytics Extensions Launchpad process that enables integration with Microsoft R Open using standard T-SQL statements. Disabling this service will make Advanced Analytics features of SQL Server unavailable.
Body.Name: MSSQLLaunchpad
Body.PathName: "C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL13.MSSQLSERVER\MSSQL\Binn\launchpad.exe" -launcher RLauncher.dll -pipename sqlsatellitelaunch -timeout 600000 -logPath "C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL13.MSSQLSERVER\MSSQL\LOG\ExtensibilityLog" -workingDir "C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL13.MSSQLSERVER\MSSQL\ExtensibilityData" -satelliteDllPath "C:\Program Files\Microsoft SQL Server\MSSQL13.MSSQLSERVER\MSSQL\Binn\sqlsatellite.dll"

Body.Caption: SQL Server (MSSQLSERVER)
Body.Description: Provides storage, processing and controlled access of data, and rapid transaction processing.
Body.Name: MSSQLSERVER

Body.Caption: Visual Studio 2015 Remote Debugger
Body.Description: Allows members of the Administrators group to remotely debug server applications using Visual Studio. Use the Visual Studio Remote Debugging Configuration Wizard to enable this service.
Body.Name: msvsmon140

Body.Caption: Network Access Protection Agent
Body.Description: The Network Access Protection (NAP) agent service collects and manages health information for client computers on a network. Information collected by NAP agent is used to make sure that the client computer has the required software and settings. If a client computer is not compliant with health policy, it can be provided with restricted network access until its configuration is updated. Depending on the configuration of health policy, client computers might be automatically updated so that users quickly regain full network access without having to manually update their computer.
Body.Name: napagent

Body.Caption: Network Connectivity Assistant
Body.Description: Provides DirectAccess status notification for UI components
Body.Name: NcaSvc

Body.Caption: Netlogon
Body.Description: Maintains a secure channel between this computer and the domain controller for authenticating users and services. If this service is stopped, the computer may not authenticate users and services and the domain controller cannot register DNS records. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: Netlogon

Body.Caption: Network Connections
Body.Description: Manages objects in the Network and Dial-Up Connections folder, in which you can view both local area network and remote connections.
Body.Name: Netman

Body.Caption: Network List Service
Body.Description: Identifies the networks to which the computer has connected, collects and stores properties for these networks, and notifies applications when these properties change.
Body.Name: netprofm

Body.Caption: Net.Tcp Port Sharing Service
Body.Description: Provides ability to share TCP ports over the net.tcp protocol.
Body.Name: NetTcpPortSharing

Body.Caption: Network Location Awareness
Body.Description: Collects and stores configuration information for the network and notifies programs when this information is modified. If this service is stopped, configuration information might be unavailable. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: NlaSvc

Body.Caption: Network Store Interface Service
Body.Description: This service delivers network notifications (e.g. interface addition/deleting etc) to user mode clients. Stopping this service will cause loss of network connectivity. If this service is disabled, any other services that explicitly depend on this service will fail to start.
Body.Name: nsi

Body.Caption: Performance Counter DLL Host
Body.Description: Enables remote users and 64-bit processes to query performance counters provided by 32-bit DLLs. If this service is stopped, only local users and 32-bit processes will be able to query performance counters provided by 32-bit DLLs.
Body.Name: PerfHost

Body.Caption: Performance Logs & Alerts
Body.Description: Performance Logs and Alerts Collects performance data from local or remote computers based on preconfigured schedule parameters, then writes the data to a log or triggers an alert. If this service is stopped, performance information will not be collected. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: pla

Body.Caption: Plug and Play
Body.Description: Enables a computer to recognize and adapt to hardware changes with little or no user input. Stopping or disabling this service will result in system instability.
Body.Name: PlugPlay

Body.Caption: IPsec Policy Agent
Body.Description: Internet Protocol security (IPsec) supports network-level peer authentication, data origin authentication, data integrity, data confidentiality (encryption), and replay protection.  This service enforces IPsec policies created through the IP Security Policies snap-in or the command-line tool "netsh ipsec".  If you stop this service, you may experience network connectivity issues if your policy requires that connections use IPsec.  Also,remote management of Windows Firewall is not available when this service is stopped.
Body.Name: PolicyAgent

Body.Caption: Power
Body.Description: Manages power policy and power policy notification delivery.
Body.Name: Power

Body.Caption: Printer Extensions and Notifications
Body.Description: This service opens custom printer dialog boxes and handles notifications from a remote print server or a printer. If you turn off this service, you won’t be able to see printer extensions or notifications.
Body.Name: PrintNotify

Body.Caption: User Profile Service
Body.Description: This service is responsible for loading and unloading user profiles. If this service is stopped or disabled, users will no longer be able to successfully sign in or sign out, apps might have problems getting to users' data, and components registered to receive profile event notifications won't receive them.
Body.Name: ProfSvc

Body.Caption: Remote Access Auto Connection Manager
Body.Description: Creates a connection to a remote network whenever a program references a remote DNS or NetBIOS name or address.
Body.Name: RasAuto

Body.Caption: Remote Access Connection Manager
Body.Description: Manages dial-up and virtual private network (VPN) connections from this computer to the Internet or other remote networks. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: RasMan

Body.Caption: Routing and Remote Access
Body.Description: Offers routing services to businesses in local area and wide area network environments.
Body.Name: RemoteAccess

Body.Caption: Remote Registry
Body.Description: Enables remote users to modify registry settings on this computer. If this service is stopped, the registry can be modified only by users on this computer. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: RemoteRegistry

Body.Caption: RPC Endpoint Mapper
Body.Description: Resolves RPC interfaces identifiers to transport endpoints. If this service is stopped or disabled, programs using Remote Procedure Call (RPC) services will not function properly.
Body.Name: RpcEptMapper

Body.Caption: Remote Procedure Call (RPC) Locator
Body.Description: In Windows 2003 and earlier versions of Windows, the Remote Procedure Call (RPC) Locator service manages the RPC name service database. In Windows Vista and later versions of Windows, this service does not provide any functionality and is present for application compatibility.
Body.Name: RpcLocator

Body.Caption: Remote Procedure Call (RPC)
Body.Description: The RPCSS service is the Service Control Manager for COM and DCOM servers. It performs object activations requests, object exporter resolutions and distributed garbage collection for COM and DCOM servers. If this service is stopped or disabled, programs using COM or DCOM will not function properly. It is strongly recommended that you have the RPCSS service running.
Body.Name: RpcSs

Body.Caption: Resultant Set of Policy Provider
Body.Description: Provides a network service that processes requests to simulate application of Group Policy settings for a target user or computer in various situations and computes the Resultant Set of Policy settings.
Body.Name: RSoPProv

Body.Caption: Special Administration Console Helper
Body.Description: Allows administrators to remotely access a command prompt using Emergency Management Services.
Body.Name: sacsvr

Body.Caption: Security Accounts Manager
Body.Description: The startup of this service signals other services that the Security Accounts Manager (SAM) is ready to accept requests.  Disabling this service will prevent other services in the system from being notified when the SAM is ready, which may in turn cause those services to fail to start correctly. This service should not be disabled.
Body.Name: SamSs

Body.Caption: Smart Card
Body.Description: Manages access to smart cards read by this computer. If this service is stopped, this computer will be unable to read smart cards. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: SCardSvr

Body.Caption: Smart Card Device Enumeration Service
Body.Description: Creates software device nodes for all smart card readers accessible to a given session. If this service is disabled, WinRT APIs will not be able to enumerate smart card readers.
Body.Name: ScDeviceEnum

Body.Caption: Task Scheduler
Body.Description: Enables a user to configure and schedule automated tasks on this computer. The service also hosts multiple Windows system-critical tasks. If this service is stopped or disabled, these tasks will not be run at their scheduled times. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: Schedule

Body.Caption: Smart Card Removal Policy
Body.Description: Allows the system to be configured to lock the user desktop upon smart card removal.
Body.Name: SCPolicySvc

Body.Caption: Secondary Logon
Body.Description: Enables starting processes under alternate credentials. If this service is stopped, this type of logon access will be unavailable. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: seclogon

Body.Caption: System Event Notification Service
Body.Description: Monitors system events and notifies subscribers to COM+ Event System of these events.
Body.Name: SENS

Body.Caption: Remote Desktop Configuration
Body.Description: Remote Desktop Configuration service (RDCS) is responsible for all Remote Desktop Services and Remote Desktop related configuration and session maintenance activities that require SYSTEM context. These include per-session temporary folders, RD themes, and RD certificates.
Body.Name: SessionEnv

Body.Caption: Internet Connection Sharing (ICS)
Body.Description: Provides network address translation, addressing, name resolution and/or intrusion prevention services for a home or small office network.
Body.Name: SharedAccess

Body.Caption: Shell Hardware Detection
Body.Description: Provides notifications for AutoPlay hardware events.
Body.Name: ShellHWDetection

Body.Caption: Microsoft Storage Spaces SMP
Body.Description: Host service for the Microsoft Storage Spaces management provider. If this service is stopped or disabled, Storage Spaces cannot be managed.
Body.Name: smphost

Body.Caption: SNMP Trap
Body.Description: Receives trap messages generated by local or remote Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) agents and forwards the messages to SNMP management programs running on this computer. If this service is stopped, SNMP-based programs on this computer will not receive SNMP trap messages. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: SNMPTRAP

Body.Caption: Print Spooler
Body.Description: This service spools print jobs and handles interaction with the printer.  If you turn off this service, you won’t be able to print or see your printers.
Body.Name: Spooler

Body.Caption: Software Protection
Body.Description: Enables the download, installation and enforcement of digital licenses for Windows and Windows applications. If the service is disabled, the operating system and licensed applications may run in a notification mode. It is strongly recommended that you not disable the Software Protection service.
Body.Name: sppsvc

Body.Caption: SQL Server Distributed Replay Client
Body.Description: One or more Distributed Replay client computers that work together with a Distributed Replay controller to simulate concurrent workloads against an instance of SQL Server.
Body.Name: SQL Server Distributed Replay Client
Body.StartName: NT Service\SQL Server Distributed Replay Client

Body.Caption: SQL Server Distributed Replay Controller
Body.Description: Provides trace replay orchestration across multiple Distributed Replay client computers.
Body.Name: SQL Server Distributed Replay Controller
Body.StartName: NT Service\SQL Server Distributed Replay Controller

Body.Caption: SQL Server Browser
Body.Description: Provides SQL Server connection information to client computers.
Body.Name: SQLBrowser

Body.Caption: SQL Server PolyBase Data Movement (MSSQLSERVER)
Body.Description: Manages communication and data transfer between SQL Server and external data sources.
Body.Name: SQLPBDMS

Body.Caption: SQL Server PolyBase Engine (MSSQLSERVER)
Body.Description: Creates, coordinates and executes the parallel query plan against external data sources.
Body.Name: SQLPBENGINE

Body.Caption: SQL Server Agent (MSSQLSERVER)
Body.Description: Executes jobs, monitors SQL Server, fires alerts, and allows automation of some administrative tasks.
Body.Name: SQLSERVERAGENT

Body.Caption: SQL Server CEIP service (MSSQLSERVER)
Body.Description: CEIP service for Sql server
Body.Name: SQLTELEMETRY

Body.Caption: SQL Server VSS Writer
Body.Description: Provides the interface to backup/restore Microsoft SQL server through the Windows VSS infrastructure.
Body.Name: SQLWriter

Body.Caption: SSDP Discovery
Body.Description: Discovers networked devices and services that use the SSDP discovery protocol, such as UPnP devices. Also announces SSDP devices and services running on the local computer. If this service is stopped, SSDP-based devices will not be discovered. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.

Body.Caption: Windows Modules Installer
Body.Description: Enables installation, modification, and removal of Windows updates and optional components. If this service is disabled, install or uninstall of Windows updates might fail for this computer.
Body.Name: TrustedInstaller

Body.Caption: User Access Logging Service
Body.Description: This service logs unique client access requests, in the form of IP addresses and user names, of installed products and roles on the local server. This information can be queried, via Powershell, by administrators needing to quantify client demand of server software for offline Client Access License (CAL) management. If the service is disabled, client requests will not be logged and will not be retrievable via Powershell queries. Stopping the service will not affect query of historical data (see supporting documentation for steps to delete historical data). The local system administrator must consult his, or her, Windows Server license terms to determine the number of CALs that are required for the server software to be appropriately licensed; use of the UAL service and data does not alter this obligation.
Body.Name: UALSVC

Body.Caption: Interactive Services Detection
Body.Description: Enables user notification of user input for interactive services, which enables access to dialogs created by interactive services when they appear. If this service is stopped, notifications of new interactive service dialogs will no longer function and there might not be access to interactive service dialogs. If this service is disabled, both notifications of and access to new interactive service dialogs will no longer function.
Body.Name: UI0Detect

Body.Caption: Remote Desktop Services UserMode Port Redirector
Body.Description: Allows the redirection of Printers/Drives/Ports for RDP connections
Body.Name: UmRdpService

Body.Caption: UPnP Device Host

Body.Caption: Credential Manager
Body.Description: Provides secure storage and retrieval of credentials to users, applications and security service packages.

Body.Description: Manages and implements Volume Shadow Copies used for backup and other purposes. If this service is stopped, shadow copies will be unavailable for backup and the backup may fail. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.

Body.Caption: Windows Time

Body.Name: W32Time

Body.Caption: W3C Logging Service
Body.Description: Provides W3C logging for Internet Information Services (IIS). If this service is stopped, W3C logging configured by IIS will not work.

Body.Caption: World Wide Web Publishing Service
Body.Description: Provides Web connectivity and administration through the Internet Information Services Manager
Body.Name: W3SVC

Body.Caption: Windows Process Activation Service
Body.Description: The Windows Process Activation Service (WAS) provides process activation, resource management and health management services for message-activated applications.

Body.Caption: Windows Connection Manager
Body.Description: Makes automatic connect/disconnect decisions based on the network connectivity options currently available to the PC and enables management of network connectivity based on Group Policy settings.
Body.Name: Wcmsvc

Body.Caption: Windows Color System
Body.Description: The WcsPlugInService service hosts third-party Windows Color System color device model and gamut map model plug-in modules. These plug-in modules are vendor-specific extensions to the Windows Color System baseline color device and gamut map models. Stopping or disabling the WcsPlugInService service will disable this extensibility feature, and the Windows Color System will use its baseline model processing rather than the vendor's desired processing. This might result in inaccurate color rendering.
Body.Name: WcsPlugInService

Body.Caption: Diagnostic Service Host
Body.Description: The Diagnostic Service Host is used by the Diagnostic Policy Service to host diagnostics that need to run in a Local Service context.  If this service is stopped, any diagnostics that depend on it will no longer function.
Body.Name: WdiServiceHost

Body.Caption: Diagnostic System Host
Body.Description: The Diagnostic System Host is used by the Diagnostic Policy Service to host diagnostics that need to run in a Local System context.  If this service is stopped, any diagnostics that depend on it will no longer function.
Body.Name: WdiSystemHost

Body.Caption: Windows Event Collector
Body.Description: This service manages persistent subscriptions to events from remote sources that support WS-Management protocol. This includes Windows Vista event logs, hardware and IPMI-enabled event sources. The service stores forwarded events in a local Event Log. If this service is stopped or disabled event subscriptions cannot be created and forwarded events cannot be accepted.
Body.Name: Wecsvc

Body.Caption: Windows Encryption Provider Host Service
Body.Description: Windows Encryption Provider Host Service brokers encryption related functionalities from 3rd Party Encryption Providers to processes that need to evaluate and apply EAS policies. Stopping this will compromise EAS compliancy checks that have been established by the connected Mail Accounts

Body.Description: Allows errors to be reported when programs stop working or responding and allows existing solutions to be delivered. Also allows logs to be generated for diagnostic and repair services. If this service is stopped, error reporting might not work correctly and results of diagnostic services and repairs might not be displayed.
Body.Name: WerSvc

Body.Caption: WinHTTP Web Proxy Auto-Discovery Service
Body.Description: WinHTTP implements the client HTTP stack and provides developers with a Win32 API and COM Automation component for sending HTTP requests and receiving responses. In addition, WinHTTP provides support for auto-discovering a proxy configuration via its implementation of the Web Proxy Auto-Discovery (WPAD) protocol.
Body.Name: WinHttpAutoProxySvc

Body.Caption: Windows Management Instrumentation
Body.Description: Provides a common interface and object model to access management information about operating system, devices, applications and services. If this service is stopped, most Windows-based software will not function properly. If this service is disabled, any services that explicitly depend on it will fail to start.
Body.Name: Winmgmt

Body.Caption: Windows Remote Management (WS-Management)
Body.Description: Windows Remote Management (WinRM) service implements the WS-Management protocol for remote management. WS-Management is a standard web services protocol used for remote software and hardware management. The WinRM service listens on the network for WS-Management requests and processes them. The WinRM Service needs to be configured with a listener using winrm.cmd command line tool or through Group Policy in order for it to listen over the network. The WinRM service provides access to WMI data and enables event collection. Event collection and subscription to events require that the service is running. WinRM messages use HTTP and HTTPS as transports. The WinRM service does not depend on IIS but is preconfigured to share a port with IIS on the same machine.  The WinRM service reserves the /wsman URL prefix. To prevent conflicts with IIS, administrators should ensure that any websites hosted on IIS do not use the /wsman URL prefix.
Body.Name: WinRM

Body.Caption: WMI Performance Adapter
Body.Description: Provides performance library information from Windows Management Instrumentation (WMI) providers to clients on the network. This service only runs when Performance Data Helper is activated.
